# Unity

Unity 6000.3.19f1. Use GameObjects, MonoBehaviours and URP. Never use DOTS, ECS or custom engine frameworks.

Use Unity New Input System. Never use the legacy Input Manager.

Prefer CharacterController. Avoid Rigidbody player movement unless requested.

Use Cinemachine when available. Keep camera separate from movement.

Prefer interface-based interactions (IInteractable). Avoid large interaction frameworks.

Keep time centralized. Systems must not manage independent clocks.

Prefer C# events. Use UnityEvents only for inspector wiring. Do not introduce generic event buses prematurely.

Prefer simple serialization. Avoid databases.

Keep combat simple. Avoid limb damage, complex armor and deep medical simulation.

Prefer simple state machines. Avoid behavior trees until necessary.

Keep crafting simple. Keep UI minimal. Keep scene count low.